# Helper Functions and Utilities

The [src/helpers](mdc:src/helpers) directory contains utility functions and helper modules used throughout the application.

## Available Helpers

### Cache Helper
[src/helpers/cache.ts](mdc:src/helpers/cache.ts)
- Manages caching mechanisms
- Improves performance by storing frequently accessed data

### Configuration Helper
[src/helpers/configHelper.ts](mdc:src/helpers/configHelper.ts)
- Handles application configuration
- Manages environment variables and settings

### Date Helper
[src/helpers/dateHelper.ts](mdc:src/helpers/dateHelper.ts)
- Date manipulation and formatting utilities
- Timezone handling and date parsing

### General Helper
[src/helpers/generalHelper.ts](mdc:src/helpers/generalHelper.ts)
- Common utility functions
- Shared helper methods

### Prompt Helper
[src/helpers/promptHelper.ts](mdc:src/helpers/promptHelper.ts)
- Manages AI prompt templates
- Handles prompt generation and formatting

## Usage
Helper functions can be imported and used across the application to maintain consistency and reduce code duplication.
